-- CORRECTED: Apollo Group posts lower quarterly earnings
-- 
-- Mon May 21, 2007 7:51pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/21/us-apollo-results-idUSWNAS207620070521

 

 (Corrects Reuters Estimates figures) 

 (Reuters) - For-profit education provider Apollo Group Inc. ( APOL.O ) posted lower quarterly earnings, but revenue for the period rose 6.7 percent. Net income fell to $60.3 million, or 35 cents a share, in its second quarter, from $79.1 million, or 45 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose to $608.7 million from $570.6 million. Excluding items, earnings were 44 cents a share. Analysts, on average, expected earnings of 47 cents a share, excluding items, on revenue of $597.1 million, according to Reuters Estimates. (Reporting by John Tilak in Bangalore)